metadata.name: Saving Trash
metadata.description:
Feeling lost and all alone  
Mind was heavy and my heart was stone  
But then I found a job that changed my fate  
Taking out the trash, it was my saving grace

Saving trash, is now what I do  
It has simply helped me make it through  
I was headed down the wrong road  
But now I'm on a path that is light and clean and I am in control

I thought that I was just a waste  
But now I see my worth, I am not a mistake  
I am proud of what I do.  It may not be grand  
But taking out the trash has helped me take a stand

Do not underestimate the power of a simple task  
It is the smallest of things that can make the biggest impact  
I am grateful for this job, it has given me a chance  
To find happiness and finally take a stance

_________________________________

Day #1 of a new journey.  The first tub filled with trash.  The first day on the job.  Some of my own garbage, from within, seems to have been tossed into the dumpsters that day as well.
